&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lucanet is looking for a driven Business Development Representative (BDR) to support pipeline generation across Singapore. This role sits at the very front of our go-to-market motion and is focused exclusively on outbound prospecting and opportunity creation.&amp;nbsp;As a BDR, your primary responsibility is to identify, engage, and qualify new prospects within our target customer segments. You will work closely with Account Executives to generate high-quality, sales-ready opportunities, acting as the first point of contact for prospective customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who is motivated by outbound activity, comfortable initiating conversations with senior stakeholders, and keen to develop a deep understanding of enterprise finance and compliance challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and engage new prospects through outbound channels, including phone, email, and social selling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research target accounts and stakeholders to personalise outreach and drive meaningful first conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify prospects against agreed criteria (e.g. ICP fit, use case, buying intent) before passing opportunities to the sales team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Book meetings and create sales-qualified opportunities for Account Executives and Account Managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Sales, Marketing, and Revenue Operations to align on target accounts, messaging, and campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date activity, lead, and opportunity data in the CRM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously refine outreach messaging based on feedback, performance data, and market insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
