&lt;h4 class=&quot;TokenisedTypography-module__EzGiEkH0__v6-3-2 TranslationField-module__fieldItemName___Q0F_7&quot;&gt;The Role&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an Executive Assistant to support our Executives in their day-to-day work and strategic priorities. You’ll keep things organized and moving behind the scenes: managing complex schedules, preparing our leaders for what’s ahead, and making sure everything stays on track in a fast-moving, global organization.&amp;nbsp;This isn’t a role where you wait for instructions. You’ll anticipate what’s needed, flag things before they become problems, and adapt quickly when the day doesn’t go as planned. You’ll work closely with teams across the business and with external partners, and you’ll report directly to our Executives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;TranslationField-module__fieldItem___g4pRX&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;TokenisedTypography-module__EzGiEkH0__v6-3-2 TranslationField-module__fieldItemName___Q0F_7&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage calendars for multiple Executives across time zones, including scheduling, resolving conflicts, and protecting time for deep work and high-priority meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take full ownership of domestic and international travel: flights, hotels, transfers, visas, and last-minute changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare meeting materials, pre-read documents, and briefings so our leaders show up to every conversation fully informed and with a clear agenda.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for internal stakeholders and external partners, ensuring communication is smooth, timely, and professional on all sides.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the connecting point between our Executives and the broader leadership team — keeping communication flowing, information current, and the right people in the loop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research topics at short notice, consolidate information from multiple sources, and deliver concise summaries that help our leadership make faster, better decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and edit presentations, strategy documents, and board-level materials – clear structure, no fluff, ready to send.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools and automation to streamline recurring workflows — from research and briefing preparation to scheduling and document drafting — so leadership time is spent where it matters most.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of internal projects that need someone reliable to drive them forward: process improvements, cross-team coordination, event logistics, and ad-hoc initiatives that don’t yet have an owner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle sensitive information about business strategy, personnel, and financials with full discretion at all times.&lt;/li&

