&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Senior QA Engineer to act as a hybrid quality champion within our engineering department. In this position, you will bridge the gap between manual and automated testing, leading the transition toward a highly automated, AI-assisted QA environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;cf0&quot;&gt;You will join a cross-functional product team that owns one of the most foundational capabilities of the Lucanet platform. It&#39;s where the platform starts: the team brings large volumes of customer data into Lucanet, organizes it into reporting entities, and that&#39;s what unlocks the entire platform for our customers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This capability underpins month-end closing and financial reporting for our customers. The team works closely with other product areas within&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Consolidation Financial Planning&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the Data Platform team to ensure reliability, scalability, and data correctness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From a quality perspective, this area comes with real complexity: high data volumes, complex business rules, and strong expectations around accuracy. The team is actively evolving how quality is owned, moving from traditional QA towards quality engineering and developer-led testing, with QA acting as a strategic partner across the full software development life cycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The core mission for this project is to implement a robust &#39;developer-led testing&#39; methodology. We are actively shifting quality responsibilities to the development team, empowering our developers to write their own tests. Your role will be to act as a quality consultant, guiding, pair-programming, and verifying the work of the developers rather than solely writing tests in isolation. You will also work closely with a wider QA community of seven automation engineers to ensure our testing strategy is scalable.&lt;/p&gt;
